---
---
<section class="how-it-works friend">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">Agent Interface</span>
    <h2>Three parts of an interface for agents</h2>

    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <h3>App publishes semantic state</h3>
        <p>Your app exposes a curated view of what it is right now — not DOM elements, not raw internals, but <em>meaning</em>.</p>
        <div class="code-block">
          <pre set:html={`<span class="fn">useSlop</span>(slop, <span class="string">"notes"</span>, {
  type: <span class="string">"collection"</span>,
  props: { count: notes.length },
  items: notes.<span class="fn">map</span>(n =&gt; ({
    id: n.id,
    props: { title: n.title },
  })),
});`} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <h3>Agent subscribes to the program</h3>
        <p>The agent subscribes to the state tree and receives patches as things change. No screenshots, polling, or repeated read tools.</p>
        <div class="code-block tree-view">
          <pre>[root] My App
  [collection] notes (count=3)
    [item] Meeting notes
    [item] Grocery list (pinned=true)
    [item] App ideas
  [status] stats (total=3, pinned=1)</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <h3>Agent invokes contextual actions</h3>
        <p>Actions live on the nodes they affect, so the agent sees what it can do in context and acts through the program directly.</p>
        <div class="code-block">
          <pre set:html={`actions: {
  <span class="fn">toggle_pin</span>: () =&gt; togglePin(note.id),
  <span class="fn">edit</span>: {
    params: { title: <span class="string">"string"</span> },
    handler: ({ title }) =&gt; updateNote(note.id, title),
  },
  <span class="fn">delete</span>: { handler: () =&gt; remove(note.id), dangerous: <span class="keyword">true</span> },
}`} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="playground-cta">
      <a href="https://playground.slopai.dev" class="btn btn-secondary">
        Try it in the playground →
      </a>
      <span class="cta-hint">Edit descriptors, inspect the tree, invoke actions, and explore the agent-facing interface live</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .how-it-works h2 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }
  .steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }
  @media (max-width: 1400px) {
    .steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  .step-number {
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--surface-container-high);
    color: var(--primary);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-machine);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .step h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  .step p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }
  .step .code-block {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .tree-view {
    color: var(--secondary);
  }
  .playground-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
  }
  .cta-hint {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }
</style>
